                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>This platform helps administrators manage complaints, feedback, and customize the system according to their needs. Below is an overview of the different sections within the Admin Dashboard:</p>

                    <div class="section-title">1. Admin Dashboard - Home Page</div>
                    <p>The Home Page of the admin dashboard gives an overview of key metrics and interactive charts to help you monitor complaints and feedback.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Complaint Status Counts:</strong> Displays the number of complaints in different statuses (Pending, In Progress, Resolved, and Rejected).</li>
                        <li><strong>Department & Year Level Complaints Charts:</strong> Shows the distribution of complaints based on department and year level.</li>
                        <li><strong>Analytics Overview:</strong> Displays trends and key metrics to help track progress over time.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="section-title">2. Complaints Page</div>
                    <p>This page allows admins to view and manage complaints submitted by students.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Table of Complaints:</strong> A table displaying important details such as Student ID, Name, Issue Type, and Status.</li>
                        <li><strong>Status Management:</strong> Admins can change complaint status (Pending, In Progress, Resolved, or Rejected).</li>
                        <li><strong>Date Formatting:</strong> The date for each complaint is formatted for easy reading.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="section-title">3. Feedback Page</div>
                    <p>Admins can view and manage feedback provided by users.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Feedback Summary:</strong> Displays total feedback, average ratings, and recommendations.</li>
                        <li><strong>Feedback Table:</strong> Displays feedback items with details such as name, rating, and suggestions.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="section-title">4. Customization Page</div>
                    <p>Admins can customize the platform's settings, theme, and features.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Theme Customization:</strong> Admins can adjust the platform's look, including logo and color scheme.</li>
                        <li><strong>Feature Settings:</strong> Allows admins to enable or disable features, adjust UI elements, and configure notifications.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="section-title">How These Pages Work Together</div>
                    <p>The Admin Dashboard serves as the central hub for managing complaints, feedback, and customization. These pages allow admins to monitor complaints, track user sentiments, and customize the system to improve user experience.</p>

                    <div class="section-title">How SafePath Works</div>
                    <p>SafePath is designed to provide a simple and secure way for students to report bullying incidents and seek support. Hereâ€™s how the system works:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Reporting Bullying:</strong> Students can report bullying incidents through the SafePath platform. They provide details about the incident, including the type of bullying, the individuals involved, and any other relevant information.</li>
                        <li><strong>Complaint Review:</strong> Once submitted, complaints are reviewed by administrators who can update the status of the complaint (e.g., pending, in progress, resolved, or rejected).</li>
                        <li><strong>Anonymous Feedback:</strong> Students can also provide anonymous feedback about their experiences with bullying, offering insights for improving the system.</li>
                        <li><strong>Support Resources:</strong> The platform also provides resources to help students deal with bullying, including counseling services, helplines, and educational materials.</li>
                    </ul>
